<td width="83%" class="lighttable">
<br />
<font class="post">
(ooc--RL has been very busy and the plot arc for Bitter Ashes has proven to be a much more ambitious undertaking than I had at first expected.  Since it takes place before Carezzia's wedding, you can see that I'm quite behind.  Still, I think it is a good tale with a good deal of insight into the personalities involved and I think it bears telling.  I should be getting back to it soon and have posted, below, a breif of the major characters in the tale to make it easier to follow the continuity.)<br /><br />Persona Dramatis:<br /><br />The Clan Destined:<br />Descourge Darkdestiny--Patriarch, adopted son of Joleena, High Preist of the Fey Court<br />Darkdestiny Descourge--Erudian, unofficial Matriarch of the clan<br />Aluleeana--Eldest child of Descourge<br />Lulee--Youngest child of Descourge<br /><br />House Rileaus:<br />Lord (R'lean) Rileaus--Patriarch, deceased<br />Lord Rene Rileaus--Youngest and only surviving son of R'lean, ward of House T'Ere<br /><br />House T'Enel:<br />High Lord T'Ere T'Enel--Patriarch, youngest High Lord to ever ascend to the Council of Nobles<br />High Lady Even'gel T'Enel--Matriarch, wife of T'Ere<br />Lord Garet T'Enel--Only child of T'Ere and T'Enel, deceased<br />Lord T'Vern T'Enel--Seneschal of the house and childhood friend of T'Ere<br /><br />The Majilenne Family:<br />Arthur Majialenne--Patriarch, staunch foe of T'Ere, deceased<br />Kathrin Majialenne--Matriarch, imprisoned by T'Ere for decades, widely considered deceased<br />Carezzia Majialenne--Only surviving child of Arthur and Kathrin, travels with the animal companion Cat, raised in seclusion by Quildluane, she is largely ignorant of her family's past<br />Kaolinn the Gentle--Unacknowledged child of Carezzia's older (now deceased) sibling<br /><br />Miscellany:<br />Dranerius--Minor noble charged with maintaining deliveries to the docks of Freeport, betrayed by the Keeper to T'Ere, deceased<br />Keeper (of the Warrens)--Menial charged with the care of T'Ere's menagerie<br />Marlowe--Fuzzy, cuddly bear<br />Princess Joleena (of the Fey Court)--Adoptive mother of Descourge, highest ranking member of the Court to interact with the mundane<br />Quildluane--Adoptive parent of Carezzia, deceased<br />Serrapoth (of the Fey Court)--High Priest of the Fey Court prior to Descourge's ascension to the position, deceased<br /> 


